3) Decision rationale:
I chose the two‑disc cinematic AOR/prog (Candidate 1) because its mix philosophy aligns more closely with the core sonic priorities I described: preserved transients and generous headroom, transparent layered guitars rather than dense overdrive, supporting keys tucked into the arrangement (matching my preference for layered keyboard textures and tasteful piano/synth accents), and dynamics‑preserving mastering that lets parts breathe. Those attributes address my main dislikes directly — the candidate avoids over‑compression and dense overdriven guitar walls, and its restrained percussion and transparent layering point to wide stereo imaging and natural placement of harmonies rather than collapsed presence‑forward vocals.
